An innovation sometimes found in Tacitus, and oc· casionally, a1s0‚ in the later writers, is the use of the Perfect sub- junctive as a potential present or imperfect in subordinate sentences ,· while, in the earlier writers (and generally, too, in Tacitus), this use was allowed only in principat or independent sentences: ut ita dixerim (Agr. 3), ut sic dixerim (Dial. 34 ).
